Citation.sTitle: Activity Coefficients at Infinite Dilution of Alkanes, Alkenes, and Alkyl Benzenes in Glycerol Using Gas-Liquid Chromatography
Citation.sAbstract: The activity coefficients at infinite dilution, ?i?, for 16 organic solutes, alkanes, alkenes, and alkyl benzenes in glycerol, have been measured by the gas-liquid chromatographic method at five temperatures from (303.15 to 343.15) K. The overall uncertainty was estimated to be about 5 %. The partial molar excess enthalpies at infinite dilution, HiE,?, of the solutes in glycerol were also derived from the temperature dependence of the ?i? values.
